#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:10
msgid ""
"An internal company document used in the purchasing process to authorize "
"the requisition of materials prior to initiating a purchase order. "
"Purchase indents are audit documents used to track the movement of "
"materials prior to their receipt by the buyer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:19
msgid "Order Type - Purchase Agreement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:21
msgid ""
"In order to create Purchase Indent, the user is given a menu under "
":menuselection:`Purchase --> Purchase Indent`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:26
msgid ""
"Select a product category, which will be used in filtering products by "
"selected category. Only those products will be listed under products "
"which belong to the selected category. The user is supposed to set the "
"number of quantity under **Request Quantity** column."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:31
msgid ""
"Once the Purchase Indent is confirmed, the user will not be able to "
"modify the document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:33
msgid ""
"Button labeled as 'Create Requisition' will appear once the Purchase "
"Indent is confirmed. By clicking over 'Create Requisition', the system "
"will pop up a parametric window, which allows user to create requisition "
"request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:39
msgid ""
"Here, the user is supposed to select any of order types, either the "
"Purchase Order or Purchase Agreement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:41
msgid ""
"Selecting Purchase Order, the user will be given another option of "
"selecting Agreement Type, either Blanket Order or Purchase Tender."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:44
msgid ""
"The user is supposed to set the number of Requisition Quantity unto "
"Remaining Quantity. The quantity must be greater than zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:47
msgid ""
"By clicking next, another window will pop up showing details of product "
"requisition. Either the user can create a purchase agreement or can "
"cancel the process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:50
msgid ""
"Once the user clicks on 'Create Purchase Agreement', the system will show"
" a smart button, which redirects to the Purchase Requisition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:53
msgid "From Purchase Requisition, the default purchase flow is to be followed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:56
msgid ":doc:`../../purchase/purchases/tender/manage_blanket_orders`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:57
msgid ":doc:`../../purchase/purchases/tender/manage_multiple_offers`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:60
msgid ""
"If the user selects the 'Purchase Tender' agreement type, then the flow "
"remains the same as directed above. For Purchase Tender, refer the above "
"link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:65
msgid "Order Type - Purchase Order"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:67
msgid "There are some products remain in product requisition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:69
msgid ""
"Now, while creating a requisition, select the order type 'Purchase Order'"
" and fill in the number of quantity under Requisition Quantity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:74
msgid ""
"By clicking over 'Next', the user is supposed to select the Vendor and "
"has to key in **Unit Price** and **Taxes**, and click over **Create "
"RFQ**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:79
msgid ""
"Here, the created purchase order will be created and there is a smart "
"button labeled as **Purchases**, which will redirect to the number of "
"purchase orders created for the current purchase indent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:83
msgid ""
"The Purchase Indent maintains the history of purchase orders and purchase"
" requisitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:88
msgid ""
"Now on, the Purchase Order workflow will be applied. For Purchase order, "
"refer the below link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:92
msgid ":doc:`../../purchase`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:95
msgid ""
"If Purchase Order or Purchase Agreement is cancelled then the quantity "
"will be updated in Purchase Indent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:99
msgid "What if there are purchase indent with same products"
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:101
msgid ""
"The scenario, where there are two or more purchase indent created and "
"such products are common among them. The system will club all those "
"common products from confirmed purchase indents while creating a "
"requisition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:107
msgid ""
"In the above image, the user can see that there are product lines with "
"different purchase indents references."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:110
msgid ""
"Whichever line is affected while creating requisition will create history"
" in respective purchase indent.  If the purchase order or purchase "
"agreement is cancelled, then the quantity of respective purchase indent "
"will be updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:116
msgid ""
"While after clicking over **Next** button, the system will add up the "
"quantity of all those same products with different number of quantity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../purchase_indent/purchase_indent.rst:119
msgid ""
"In requisition request, the **Graphics Card** is having the number of "
"quantity of 5 and 2 respectively. So the system will merge up the number "
"of quantity while creating purchase order or purchase agreement."
msgstr ""

